-- pitfalls --

DST spring-forward silently skips scheduled fires. a job scheduled at
"30 2 * * *" (2:30 AM daily) skips entirely on the day clocks jump from
2:00 to 3:00 AM because 2:30 AM does not exist. the parser uses
Date.setHours which adjusts to 3:30, then the hour check fails and
advances to the next day. no warning, no error, the job just doesn't
run that day.
